      "fix_scope": "multi_file_refactor",
      "confidence": "high",
      "issues_preventing_higher_score": "No automated boundary guard exists here for ID/token schema drift between contract identity and action token derivation; a single changed naming convention requires coordinated updates across multiple modules without compile-time protection."
    },
    "test_strategy": {
      "evidence": [
        "README mandates contract-gate coverage and explicit per-contract lifecycle-policy assertions for changed catalog entries in `goseg/protocol/contracts/contracts_test.go` and related contract files.",
        "In scope, `goseg/protocol/contracts/protocol_contracts.go` and `goseg/protocol/contracts/startram_contracts.go` only define catalog specs and metadata wiring, with no local assertions protecting contract compatibility policy or lifecycle semantics.",
        "README treats these contract surfaces as governance-critical boundaries for upload/C2C/StarTram flows, but the files themselves have no immediate self-documenting test hooks or invariant checks."
      ],
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "multi_file_refactor",
      "confidence": "medium"
    }
  },
  "findings": [
    {
      "dimension": "cross_module_architecture",
      "identifier": "protocol-token-prefix-derivation",
      "summary": "Contract token derivation is coupled to literal namespace prefixes, creating cross-module contract-shape fragility.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/protocol/contracts/protocol_contracts.go",
        "README.md"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`protocol_contracts.go` defines `actionTokenOpenEndpoint`, `actionTokenReset`, and `actionTokenConnect` by slicing hardcoded prefixes from `UploadActionOpenEndpoint`, `UploadActionReset`, and `C2CConnectAction`.",
        "This embeds textual wire-level shape (`protocol.actions.upload.`, `protocol.actions.c2c.`) into action-token generation logic instead of using a single contract constructor or schema-level API."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Replace manual prefix slicing with a central contract constructor/parser in the contracts package (e.g., `actionTokenFromContractID` with compile-time tests) and have all protocol and StarTram entries use it so namespace/ID changes cannot desynchronize action tokens.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "module",
      "fix_scope": "single_edit",
      "root_cause_cluster": "contract_schema_duplication"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "test_strategy",
      "identifier": "contract-governance-gap",
      "summary": "Contract lifecycle/compatibility expectations in governance docs are not locally enforced at the contract surface.",
      "related_files": [
        "README.md",
        "goseg/protocol/contracts/protocol_contracts.go",
        "goseg/protocol/contracts/startram_contracts.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "README lists a strict contract governance contract for protocol/StarTram surfaces (including explicit lifecycle-policy checks, gate coverage, and compatibility descriptor assertions).",
        "The two contract surface files only expose static descriptors and delegated metadata lookups and do not include direct invariants for required lifecycle fields."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Add focused unit tests adjacent to the contract package (in existing contract test file) that assert descriptor completeness and compatibility policy invariants per contract ID, so updates to these tables fail fast before entering CI and before downstream consumers diverge.",
      "confidence": "medium",
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "multi_file_refactor",
      "root_cause_cluster": "contract_schema_duplication"
    }
  ],
  "retrospective": {
    "root_causes": [
      "String-shape coupling between contract IDs and action tokens, rather than explicit contract-domain abstractions.",
      "Governance policy is centrally documented but not mirrored as immediate invariants in contract declaration modules."
    ],
    "likely_symptoms": [
      "protocol-token-prefix-derivation",
      "contract-governance-gap"
    ],
